Government Enterprise Pack Compliance Evidence Generator
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line proficiency
Understanding of JSON and YAML formats
Familiarity with log file structures
Basic Python scripting knowledge
Understanding of compliance concepts (audit trails, evidence collection)
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Generate compliance artifacts for government enterprise environments
Create automated audit evidence reports
Produce structured logs for compliance verification
Implement evidence collection workflows using open-source tools
Environment Setup
You will use the Al Nafi bare-metal Linux machine provided via the "Start Lab" button. All tools will be installed during this lab.

Install Required Tools
# Update package manager
sudo apt update

# Install Python and pip
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip python3-venv

# Install additional utilities
sudo apt install -y jq git curl

# Create project directory
mkdir -p ~/compliance-lab
cd ~/compliance-lab

# Create Python virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install Python packages
pip install pyyaml jinja2 python-dateutil
